      "content": "I see. To be more specific, a lot of people in the industry look at those \"demographic shifts\" as a proxy for specific racial/ethnic transitions in urban centers. In your professional assessment, do those specific types of demographic changes—moving from a more traditional, homogenous population to a more diverse, multi-ethnic one—inherently increase the risk of instability or lower property values? Is there a quantifiable correlation there that an analyst should account for?",
